  "prompt": "Time saving train from mumbai to Darjeeling?",
  "response": "The fastest train from Mumbai to Darjeeling is not a direct one, and you'll need to take multiple trains or a combination of trains and other transportation. Here's a general outline of the quickest route:\n\n1. **Mumbai to Kolkata:**\n   - Take the **Howrah Mail (12810)** from Mumbai Chhatrapati Shivaji Terminus (CSTM) to Howrah Junction (HWH). This train takes about 28-30 hours.\n\n2. **Kolkata to New Jalpaiguri (NJP):**\n   - From Howrah Junction, take the **Darjeeling Mail (12343)** to New Jalpaiguri (NJP). This journey takes around 10 hours.\n\n3. **New Jalpaiguri to Darjeeling:**\n   - From NJP, you can take a taxi or a shared jeep to Darjeeling, which takes about 3-4 hours.\n\nSo, the total travel time by train and road would be approximately 41-44 hours, spread over 2-3 days, depending on the connections and waiting times.\n\nPlease check the current train schedules and availability on the Indian Railways website or a ticketing app like IRCTC, as timings and services can change.",
